# Proposal for User Research Study - Product Dashboard Redesign

Dear Sarah,

Thank you for your positive response to our Agile Workshop proposal. During our conversation, you mentioned that your product team is also struggling with your internal analytics dashboard - users find it confusing and rarely use it effectively.

We'd like to propose a focused user research study to understand why the dashboard isn't working and what your team actually needs.

# Context

Your product team uses an internal analytics dashboard daily to track KPIs, user behavior, and product performance. However, feedback suggests that:

- Important metrics are hard to find
- The interface is cluttered and overwhelming
- Different team members need different views but get the same dashboard
- Data is there, but insights are hidden

This is impacting decision-making speed and data-driven culture.

# Objectives

Conduct a rapid user research study to:

- Understand how different roles use (or don't use) the dashboard
- Identify pain points and unmet needs
- Map out ideal workflows for different user types
- Provide actionable recommendations for dashboard improvements



---

- Kickoff meeting with stakeholders
- 8-10 user interviews (Product Managers, Analysts, Engineers)
- 4 contextual inquiry sessions (observe people using dashboard in real work)
- Current dashboard audit (UX heuristics evaluation)
- Analytics review (which features are actually used?)

# 2. Analysis & Synthesis (Week 2)

- User persona refinement (dashboard usage patterns)
- Pain point mapping
- Needs prioritization (must-have vs nice-to-have)
- Comparative analysis (best practices from similar tools)

# 3. Recommendations & Roadmap (Week 3)

- Research findings presentation (with video clips)
- Quick-win improvements (can be done immediately)
- Redesign recommendations (with sketches/wireframes)

Dear Dr. Richter,

AI-powered document processing for your invoice and contract management workflows.
Context
FinanceHub currently processes 500+ invoices and contracts manually each month. Your
team spends approximately 40 hours per month on data entry, verification, and filing. You've
identified AI-powered document processing as a potential solution but need to validate
technical feasibility, accuracy, and ROI before committing to a full implementation.

This POC will:
- Test AI document extraction accuracy with your real documents
- Evaluate integration feasibility with your existing systems (SAP, Salesforce)
- Demonstrate end-to-end workflow automation
- Provide data-driven ROI analysis
- Deliver a technical architecture proposal for full implementation

contracts) and iteratively improve accuracy through model training and validation. The POC
will run in a sandboxed environment with no impact on production systems.

# Proposal for User Research Study - Product Dashboard Redesign

Dear Sarah,

Thank you for your positive response to our Agile Workshop proposal. During our conversation, you mentioned that your product team is also struggling with your internal analytics dashboard - users find it confusing and rarely use it effectively.

We'd like to propose a focused user research study to understand why the dashboard isn't working and what your team actually needs.

# Context

Your product team uses an internal analytics dashboard daily to track KPIs, user behavior, and product performance. However, feedback suggests that:

- Important metrics are hard to find
- The interface is cluttered and overwhelming
- Different team members need different views but get the same dashboard
- Data is there, but insights are hidden

This is impacting decision-making speed and data-driven culture.

# Objectives

Conduct a rapid user research study to:

- Understand how different roles use (or don't use) the dashboard
- Identify pain points and unmet needs
- Map out ideal workflows for different user types
- Provide actionable recommendations for dashboard improvements



---

- Kickoff meeting with stakeholders
- 8-10 user interviews (Product Managers, Analysts, Engineers)

# 2. Analysis & Synthesis (Week 2)

- User persona refinement (dashboard usage patterns)
- Pain point mapping
- Needs prioritization (must-have vs nice-to-have)

Dear Dr. Richter,

identified AI-powered document processing as a potential solution but need to validate
technical feasibility, accuracy, and ROI before committing to a full implementation.

- Evaluate integration feasibility with your existing systems (SAP, Salesforce)

We'll build a working prototype using a subset of your documents (50 invoices, 20

contracts) and iteratively improve accuracy through model training and validation. The POC
will run in a sandboxed environment with no impact on production systems.

- System integration assessment (SAP, Salesforce APIs)

- AI model selection and configuration

# Proposal for User Research Study - Product Dashboard Redesign

Dear Sarah,

Thank you for your positive response to our Agile Workshop proposal. During our conversation, you mentioned that your product team is also struggling with your internal analytics dashboard - users find it confusing and rarely use it effectively.

We'd like to propose a focused user research study to understand why the dashboard isn't working and what your team actually needs.

# Context

Your product team uses an internal analytics dashboard daily to track KPIs, user behavior, and product performance. However, feedback suggests that:

- Important metrics are hard to find
- The interface is cluttered and overwhelming
- Different team members need different views but get the same dashboard
- Data is there, but insights are hidden

This is impacting decision-making speed and data-driven culture.

# Objectives

Conduct a rapid user research study to:

- Understand how different roles use (or don't use) the dashboard
- Identify pain points and unmet needs
- Map out ideal workflows for different user types

# 2. Analysis & Synthesis (Week 2)

- User persona refinement (dashboard usage patterns)
- Pain point mapping
- Needs prioritization (must-have vs nice-to-have)
- Comparative analysis (best practices from similar tools)

- Research findings presentation (with video clips)
- Quick-win improvements (can be done immediately)

- Clean, contemporary design aligned with your brand
- Mobile-first approach (60%+ of your traffic is mobile)
- Integration with your existing inventory management system
- Secure payment processing
- Customer account management
- Product search and filtering capabilities
- Admin dashboard for content and product management

Approach
We'll use an agile development approach with two-week sprints, allowing for regular
feedback and adjustments. Our team will work closely with your stakeholders to ensure the

Proposal for a Two-Day Agile Transformation Workshop
Dear Sarah,
Thank you for your inquiry and your interest in working with us on your agile
transformation journey.
We are pleased to present you with a proposal for a two-day workshop on Agile
Transformation - specifically tailored to the needs and dynamics of your product
development team.
Context
Your product team is transitioning from waterfall to agile methodologies and needs
hands-on support. The team has heard about Scrum and Kanban but lacks practical
experience implementing these frameworks in a real business context.
The goal of this workshop is to provide your team with foundational agile knowledge,
practical tools, and a clear implementation roadmap for your upcoming product releases.
Objectives
This workshop will deliver a comprehensive understanding of agile principles, values,
methods, tools and limitations - with the goal of creating a shared foundation for agile
working within your team. We'll focus on practical application in product development
contexts, with special attention to roles like Product Owner and Scrum Master.
Approach
The workshop will be facilitated by experienced consultants from Momentum Digital and
combines theory, group work, and hands-on exercises. Content will be delivered based on
real challenges from your daily work, not in "textbook mode."

Services
1. Preparation & Alignment
- Status assessment via email questionnaire to team leads (5-6 questions about current
practices, pain points, project examples)
- Workshop agenda customization based on assessment
- 2 feedback loops via video call (1 hour each) to finalize agenda
- Creation and distribution of workshop materials for review
2. Workshop Delivery (2 Days)
- Facilitation by two experienced Senior Consultants from Momentum Digital
- Day 1: 9 AM - 5 PM, Day 2: 9 AM - 4 PM
- On-site at your offices, including breaks and lunch
3. Follow-up & Documentation
- Digital booklet as PDF (methodology slides + results documentation)
- 30-day follow-up check-in call (1 hour)
Timeline
The workshop is tentatively scheduled for December 2025. We have pre-blocked December
10-11 or December 16-17, 2025.
Preparation begins approximately 3 weeks prior. Workshop documentation will be delivered
within 1 week after completion.
Commercial Terms
For this project, we anticipate the following effort:
Phase Roles Effort (Person Days) Cost (EUR, net)
Preparation Director Product 1.0 1,500

Senior Consultant 2.0
Delivery Director Product 2.0 4,000

Junior Consultant 0.5
Total (EUR, net) 6,500
All prices are in Euro and exclude 19% VAT.
Billing is based on actual effort and roles assigned to the project. Should significant
deviations in effort (+/- 20%) occur, Momentum Digital will inform you promptly.
Validity
This proposal is valid for 90 days.
Contract Acceptance
Acceptance of this proposal must be in written form.
Payment Terms
Actual project costs based on effort and assigned roles will be invoiced upon project
completion.
We look forward to collaborating with you and are available for any questions.
